  "text": "## Envoy TLS Certificate Validation Analysis\n\n### Summary\n\nFound 27 C++ source files in Envoy v1.31.2 under `source/common/tls/` and `source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/` that contain certificate verification logic. These files handle both server certificate validation (on client side) and client certificate validation (on server side).\n\n### Server Certificate Validation (Client-Side)\n\nWhen Envoy acts as a client, it validates SERVER certificates through:\n\n1. **Entry Point**: `client_context_impl.cc` and `client_ssl_socket.cc` create client TLS contexts\n2. **Verification Callback**: `context_impl.cc` registers `customVerifyCallback()` via `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify()` (line 181)\n3. **Core Validation**: `cert_validator/default_validator.cc` performs verification via `doVerifyCertChain()` method which:\n   - Calls `X509_verify_cert(ctx.get())` (line 315) for OpenSSL certificate chain verification\n   - Validates Subject Alt Names (SANs)\n   - Verifies certificate hashes and SPKI values\n   - Uses `X509_STORE_CTX` for chain validation\n\n### Client Certificate Validation (Server-Side)\n\nWhen Envoy acts as a server, it validates CLIENT certificates through:\n\n1. **Configuration**: `server_context_impl.cc` configures server contexts\n2. **Client CA Setup**: Calls `cert_validator_->addClientValidationContext()` (line 147 in server_context_impl.cc) which:\n   - Sets up CA certificate list using `SSL_CTX_set_client_CA_list()`\n   - Configures `SSL_CTX_set_verify()` with `SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT` flags (line 528 in default_validator.cc)\n   - Sets `SSL_CTX_set_verify_depth()` (line 540 in default_validator.cc)\n3. **Verification**: Uses same `customVerifyCallback` flow as server validation\n\n### Key Functions and Their Purposes\n\n**SSL_CTX_set_verify** (source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc:528)\n- Configures certificate verification requirements for client certificates\n- Sets SSL_VERIFY_PEER to request client certificates\n- Sets SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT to fail if client cert is missing\n\n**X509_verify_cert** (source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc:315)\n- OpenSSL core function that performs X.509 certificate chain validation\n- Validates certificate signatures, dates, CRLs, and trust chain\n- Returns 1 for success, 0 for verification failure\n\n**customVerifyCallback** (source/common/tls/context_impl.cc:474)\n- Custom verification callback registered with OpenSSL\n- Handles both server and client certificate validation\n- Orchestrates asynchronous and synchronous validation\n- Checks if certificate validation is pending or already completed\n\n**addClientValidationContext** (source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc:481)\n- Sets up CA certificate list for client certificate validation\n- Extracts CA certificate subject names\n- Prevents duplicate CA entries\n- Critical for server-side client certificate validation\n\n### Alternative Validator: SPIFFE\n\nFile: `source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc`\n\nProvides an alternative certificate validator with SPIFFE-specific logic:\n- Uses same `X509_verify_cert` approach (line 177)\n- Implements `addClientValidationContext()` for client certificate setup (line 108)\n- Adds SPIFFE-specific certificate precheck and SAN matching\n- Supports multiple trust domains\n\n### Error Handling\n\nFile: `source/common/tls/utility.cc` line 457\n- `getX509VerificationErrorInfo()` extracts detailed error information from OpenSSL\n- Uses `X509_verify_cert_error_string()` to get human-readable error messages\n- Critical for debugging certificate validation failures\n\n### Verification Mode Constants\n\nBoth validators use OpenSSL verification mode flags:\n- `SSL_VERIFY_NONE`: No verification\n- `SSL_VERIFY_PEER`: Request peer certificate\n- `SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT`: Fail if peer certificate is missing\n\nThese are set during context initialization in `initializeSslContexts()` method and used throughout the validation pipeline.\n\n### Configuration Flow\n\n1. **Context Creation**: `context_impl.cc` creates SSL contexts\n2. **Validator Initialization**: Cert validator factory creates appropriate validator (default or SPIFFE)\n3. **Callback Registration**: `customVerifyCallback` is registered via `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify`\n4. **Handshake**: During TLS handshake, OpenSSL calls `customVerifyCallback`\n5. **Chain Verification**: Calls `doVerifyCertChain()` which uses `X509_verify_cert`\n6. **Result**: Returns validation status to OpenSSL\n"
